[{"_path":"/legacy-articles/2018-02-19-citizenship-in-a-republic","_dir":"legacy-articles","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"en","_empty":false,"title":"老羅斯福演講：民主國家的公民權利","description":"","excerpt":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"以下摘錄自《Scrum，用一半的時間做兩倍的事》"},{"type":"element","tag":"sup","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"#user-content-fn-1","ariaDescribedBy":"footnote-label","dataFootnoteRef":true,"id":"user-content-fnref-1"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"1"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"。原文為美國總統老羅斯福於 1910 年在巴黎索邦大學的演說「民主國家的公民權利」（Citizenship in a Republic）"},{"type":"element","tag":"sup","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"#user-content-fn-2","ariaDescribedBy":"footnote-label","dataFootnoteRef":true,"id":"user-content-fnref-2"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"2"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"。"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"blockquote","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"榮耀並不屬於批評的人，亦不屬於指出勇者如何失敗，或點出別人哪裡應該做的更好的人。榮耀屬於實際身處在競技場中、臉上沾滿塵土與血汗，仍英勇奮戰的勇者；他們會犯錯，而且一錯再錯，因為錯誤與缺失必會伴隨努力而來；但是他們都確切地知道要奮戰不懈、知道要充滿熱誠、全心投入；獻身於崇高的志業。他們最好的結局是終於功成名就；就算失敗，最差的下場只不過就是在勇敢奮戰後落敗。他們的定位，絕非那些冷漠懦弱、不知勝利與失敗為何物的人所能相提並論。"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"附上摘自 Wiki 的原文版"},{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"^3"}]},{"type":"text","value":"："}]},{"type":"element","tag":"blockquote","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It is not the critic who counts;"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nnot the man who points out how the strong man stumbles,"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nor where the doer of deeds could have done them better."},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nThe credit belongs to the man who is actually in the arena,"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nwhose face is marred by dust and sweat and blood;"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nwho strives valiantly; who errs,"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nwho comes short again and again,"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nbecause there is no effort without error and shortcoming;"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nbut who does actually strive to do the deeds;"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nwho knows great enthusiasms,"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nthe great devotions;"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nwho spends himself in a worthy cause;"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nwho at the best knows in the end the triumph of high achievement,"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nand who at the worst,"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nif he fails,"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nat least fails while daring greatly,"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"\nso that his place shall never be with those cold and timid souls who neither know victory nor defeat."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"section","props":{"className":["footnotes"],"dataFootnotes":true},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"className":["sr-only"],"id":"footnote-label"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Footnotes"}]},{"type":"element","